  "prompt": "I didn't kiss on the first date, is this bad and what should I do from this point on?",
  "response": "It's completely normal not to kiss on the first date, and it isn't inherently bad at all. Every relationship moves at its own pace, and what's most important is that both you and your date feel comfortable and respected. Here are some steps you can take moving forward:\n\n1. **Reflect on the Date:**\n   - **Connection:** Think about how you felt during the date. Did you enjoy the conversation and the time spent together?\n   - **Comfort Level:** Assess whether you both seemed comfortable and engaged with each other.\n\n2. **Communicate Openly:**\n   - **Express Interest:** If you're interested in seeing them again, let them know! A simple message expressing that you had a good time can set the stage for another date.\n   - **Discuss Boundaries:** If topics around physical intimacy come up, communicate your feelings honestly.\n\n3. **Take Your Time:**\n   - **Natural Progression:** Let the relationship develop naturally without feeling pressured to reach a specific milestone quickly.\n   - **Build Trust:** Focus on building emotional intimacy, which often leads to physical intimacy when both parties are ready.\n\n4. **Be Understanding:**\n   - **Respect Boundaries:** Both you and your date may have different comfort levels regarding physical affection. Respect each other's boundaries without judgment.\n   - **Different Paces:** Recognize that everyone moves at their own pace in relationships. What's important is mutual respect and understanding.\n\n5. **Plan for Future Dates:**\n   - **Build More Memories:** Engage in activities that allow you both to get to know each other better in different settings.\n   - **Increase Comfort:** As you spend more time together, you might naturally feel more comfortable sharing intimate moments like a first kiss.\n\n6. **Stay Positive:**\n   - **No Pressure:** Avoid putting pressure on yourself or the situation. Not kissing on the first date can sometimes lead to a deeper, more meaningful connection.\n   - **Focus on Compatibility:** Use this time to assess overall compatibility beyond just physical attraction.\n\nRemember, there's no right or wrong timeline for how a relationship should progress. What's most important is that both you and your partner feel comfortable and mutually interested in taking the next steps together. Trust your instincts and communicate openly, and things will unfold naturally.",
